      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A strategist class uses this random source when you call the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkstrategist/1501118-bestmoveforactiveplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. Different strategist classes use randomization in different ways:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "newTerm",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "deterministic"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " strategy, such as that of the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkminmaxstrategist"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " class, can reach states where multiple moves are rated the most desirable. In such cases, the strategist can randomly choose from among the best possible moves, making the behavior of a computer-controlled player appear more natural and unpredictable."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If this property is set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "nil"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " (the default), the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkminmaxstrategist"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " class method does not randomize—that is, when repeatedly presented with the same set of equally-optimal moves, the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkstrategist/1501118-bestmoveforactiveplayer"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method always makes the same choice."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "newTerm",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "probabilistic"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " strategy, such as that of the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkmontecarlostrategist"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " class, "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "emphasis",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "requires"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " a random source in order to randomly explore the set of possible moves."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If this property is set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "nil"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " (the default), the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkmontecarlostrategist"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " class throws an exception when you call the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkstrategist/1501118-bestmoveforactiveplayer"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A randomizer is any object that implements the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrandom"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " protocol, such as the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrandomsource"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrandomdistribution"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " classes and their subclasses. Choosing a separate randomizer instance from that used by other systems in your game ensures that the randomization of moves is independent; that is, the strategist's selection of moves does not depend on your game’s other uses of randomization APIs. You can also use randomizer classes to reproduce a specific sequence of random actions for debugging, and to fine-tune the randomization behavior."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
